api.syntaxerror.phpjavabridge.PacketHandler

  • Uses of PacketHandler in api.syntaxerror.phpjavabridge

    Methods in api.syntaxerror.phpjavabridge with parameters of type PacketHandler 
    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void Bridge.setDefaultPacketHandler​(PacketHandler handler)
    If a Packet couldn't be handled (because there was no PacketHandler set via Bridge.setPacketHandler(PacketHandler, int...)), this handler is called.

    If there is no default PacketHandler either, a UnsupportedOperationException is thrown.
    void Bridge.setPacketHandler​(PacketHandler handler, int... pids)
    Defines a PacketHandler for specific Packet-IDs.

    If there is no PacketHandler defined for a Packet-ID and no default Packet is set via Bridge.setDefaultPacketHandler(PacketHandler), a UnsupportedOperationException is thrown if such a Packet is received
